The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 Mumbai, June 6: Sun Pharmaceutical Industries has posted a 46.01 per cent increase in net profit at Rs 115.89 crore for the quarter ended March 31 compared with Rs 79.37 crore in the corresponding previous period. Total income grew 48.79 per cent to Rs 454.43 crore from Rs 305.41 crore, the company informed stock exchanges. The shares of the company closed at Rs 763.90, down 3.94per cent, on the BSE today.

 Mumbai, June 6: AstraZeneca Pharma India has split its equity shares in the ratio of 1:5. The EGM held today approved the split, in which one equity share of Rs 10 would be split into five shares of Rs 2.

 Calcutta, June 6: Balmer Lawrie amp; Co has reported a net profit of Rs 46.80 crore in 2005-06, against Rs 29.83 crore in the previous fiscal. Net sales was recorded at Rs 1,244.33 crore compared with Rs 996.55 crore in the year-ago period.

 Mumbai, June 6: BOC India has signed a long-term contract with JSW Steel for supply of over 3,000 tonnes per day of gaseous oxygen, nitrogen and argon.

 Shanghai, June 6: China will let local subsidiaries of overseas businesses buy strategic stakes in its public companies from July 1, the Chinese government said. The subsidiaries will be regarded as overseas shareholders.




